📣 Join WiCS’ 2024-25 high school mentorship program! 💙

As a mentor, you will have the chance to be partnered with a female high school student interested in tech and share your experiences to guide them through what it’s like to pursue a technical degree. Becoming a mentor is an excellent way to have a positive impact on someone’s life, while developing your leadership and interpersonal skills!

We’re opening applications until October 7th 11:59 PM. Application link is in our bio!

Also, feel free to reach out to any high school students that may be interested in joining this program! Sign-up link is in our bio!

- Note: you do not have to identify as a female in order to apply to become a mentor. We are looking for all individuals who are friendly, inclusive, and committed to supporting women in tech. 💙

Is there a phriend who stood out to you in September? A classmate who went above and beyond? A pharmacy student who is simply impressive? Let us know because we want to acknowledge it!

Each month, UPS wants to celebrate the contributions and achievements of our students in a fun and memorable way. We will be giving a shout-out to multiple students across all 4 years every month on our social media so don’t hold back!

Those who receive multiple nominations will choose a nomination of their choice for our social media! To enter your submission, please use the link in our bio to tell us who you are acknowledging and why (1-2 sentences max).

The deadline to nominate a phriend is October 4th, 2024 at 11:59pm. We look forward to seeing your submissions and encourage you to nominate your peers!!!
